  "text": "Next we describe the 6-dimensional descendants of nilpotent Lie algebras with dimension at most 5. The Lie algebras in this section are given with multiplication tables with respect to fixed bases with trivial products of the form [x i , x j ] = 0 omitted. With respect to the list of [CITATION_1] we have made a few small changes. The multiplication table of L 6,19 (ε), for ε = 0, is different from (but isomorphic to) the Lie algebra denoted with the same symbol in [CITATION_2] . The Lie algebras L 6,19 (0) and L 6,21 (0) from [CITATION_3] are denoted here by L 6,27 and L 6,28 , respectively. We have made these changes because the structure of L 6,k (ǫ), k = 19, 21, is different for ε = 0 and ε = 0. Furthermore, in characteristic 2 a few new algebras appear that are not contained in [CITATION_4] . These Lie algebras are L",
